BMW has unveiled the pricing of the new 3-Series for South Africa, as reported by Wheels24. The report stated that only the 320d and 330i models will be sold in SA. Other models in the international line-up include the 320i, 318d, 320d xDrive, and 330d. The new pricing is: The report added that the cars are expected to arrive in the country by March 2019. At R649,253 for the 320d, the pricing has made the new 3-Series almost as expensive the BMW M2 manual when it launched in 2016. Its local price at the time was R791,000.